cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 90 miles (145 km) southeast of Cozumel, Mexico
cyclone.trajectory: moving northwest toward the northern Yucatán this evening, then turning north and accelerating northeast toward the northern Gulf Coast on Wednesday and the Mid-Atlantic late Thursday
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: northern Gulf Coast (likely southeast Louisiana to Mississippi coast)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Storm-Surge Watch Intracoastal City LA to Navarre FL; Hurricane Watch Morgan City LA to MS/AL border including Lake Pontchartrain; Tropical Storm Watch MS/AL border to Okaloosa/Walton Co. FL and west of Morgan City to Intracoastal City LA
weather_observation.warning_coast: Hurricane Warning Tulum to Dzilam Mexico (including Cozumel); Tropical Storm Warning south of Tulum to Punta Allen and west of Dzilam to Progreso Mexico
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Gulf Coast from Louisiana to Florida Panhandle, then inland across the Southeast and Mid-Atlantic (including Chesapeake Bay and Maryland coasts)
weather_observation.wind: Gusty winds 25-40 mph possible late Thu night–Fri morning as the remnant low passes nearby
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor tidal rise of 1–2 ft possible along upper Chesapeake Bay coincident with onshore flow
weather_observation.rainfall: 2–4 inches of rainfall expected Thursday night into Friday, locally higher amounts possible
weather_observation.other_hazards: Brief river and urban flooding in low-lying areas; reduced visibility and slippery surfaces affecting cargo handling and road/rail access
